message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV. The paper discusses a natural language processing task, specifically machine comprehension of text, which falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed architecture is based on neural networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Pointer Net, a sequence-to-sequence model, also suggests a possible connection to neural networks used in natural language generation (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
